      • splitNodePath

        String[] splitNodePath(String path)
        Split the provided path into a string array suitable for accessing the correct configuration children. Normally this just splits the path with the getPathSeparator(), but can limit how deep a child path can go or whether this configuration can even have children.
        Parameters:
        path - The path to split
        Returns:
        The connectly split path.

      • ensureCorrectPath

        String[] ensureCorrectPath(String[] rawPath)
        Make sure the provided path meets the requirements. A correct implementation of Configuration will impose the same restrictions on this and splitNodePath(String), so invoking this method on an array from splitNodePath(String) would return the original array.
        Parameters:
        rawPath - The raw path of the configuration
        Returns:
        The corrected input path
